The '''Lu Xun Literary Institute''' (鲁迅文学院), located in [[Beijing]], is China's only national academy in literature education. Established in 1950 as the '''Central Literary Research Institute''' (中央文学研究所), it was closed in 1957 due to the [[Anti-Rightist Movement]] and not reopened until 1980. The current name, after the prominent literary figure [[Lu Xun]], was adapted in 1984.<ref>http://contemporary_chinese_culture.academic.ru/481/Lu_Xun_Literary_Institute</ref>



